And again, I'm correct on the numbers. From the MOU: The total cost of "the project" (which is both the stadium and the practice/athletic fields) is 280M.
text_html: I care because _Im on a thread comparing the Columbus and Austin proposals_ And again, I'm correct on the numbers. From the MOU: The total cost of "the project" (which is both the stadium and the practice/athletic fields) is 280M.

text:
The MOU explicitly details $50M from the city, (now) $45M from the county, and now a new $45M from other public sources. Then states that the balance of the 280M comes from private(JHAC).
It's simple subtraction.

text: Exactly. Pendules are not "drippings". They are formed from the interaction of the two wake vortices of the aircraft which generates small secondary vortices. These then shape the contrail. It's very normal to see pendules on contrails.
text_html: Exactly. Pendules are not "drippings". They are formed from the interaction of the two wake vortices of the aircraft which generates small secondary vortices. These then shape the contrail. It's very normal to see pendules on contrails.
